<subSubSection id="35B0DF17896A2BF3D6171424E9281B1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="29B3FD64033660C6EE800E9D6E55A1D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="054E007DC0DA49C2D93F1D81AE91CBF2" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
The species name refers to the clear affinity of this taxon to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="0D0848979546E7846EE4614298C4EC0D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Klaprothia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Klaprothia" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AA8BC77027A885D6B4F5122F109C0AD8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Klaprothia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kunth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4DE30AF77E5BE64EF661D21383092F87" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="496D27FE3795667F4C45DD73937BB529" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC355DB64993A3CFB6E0DB07CF48B4F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="FF782CEF8FBD0A157C317FA047E99349" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Xylopodia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xylopodia klaprothioides" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klaprothioides">
<emphasis id="656568EAEF92802410B47667DB47E596" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Xylopodia klaprothioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to a small area of the Pacific slope of the Cordillera Occidental in Andean NW Peru. It is a very narrowly endemic species, known from only two localities some 8 km apart (in a direct line) in Dpto. Cajamarca Prov. 
<normalizedToken id="193B5E4CA161456ABA59C62EC9FF7F43" originalValue="Contumazá">Contumaza</normalizedToken>
, at elevations from ca. 2,500-3,000 m (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4492E01AE1432B591B42FDFA09A79462" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Known distribution of Xylopodia klaprothioides and X. laurensis (photo credit for La Paz: A. F. Fuentes)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.194.77827.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/673018" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7C975F9E18736907C3B4390FFD3193F" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="A8076E6F7A896B7F8AA02A6AD8E1B088" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5ACD4CDDBC2FE2938423672FA79DF401" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="6CD6EB00BA5B8B7C803A56733AB1269E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Xylopodia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xylopodia klaprothioides" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klaprothioides">
<emphasis id="3543FABDACA93B4A8BDFBAEEE5F860C6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Xylopodia klaprothioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in seasonally dry Andean scrub habitats, mostly around hedges and gullies, often on rocky soil dominated by xeric adapted shrubs, small trees and other vegetation including 
<taxonomicName id="1F5C203EB2FF5F1BAA2C1315445AFE2E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Cylindropuntia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cylindropuntia" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E075862C83785983BFC2B65B3F0F87FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Cylindropuntia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Engelm.) F.M. Knuth and terrestrial bromeliads (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="50E479C6F66C46EDA3F7EA55F568E91D" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Habitats of Xylopodia. A deciduous forest near Jujuy, Argentina, habitat of X. laurensis B X. laurensis habitat in a dry creek near Chuquisaca, Bolivia C rocky slopes with xerophilous vegetation near the town of Contumaza, Peru, habitat of narrowly endemic X. klaprothioides." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.194.77827.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/673021" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">4C</figureCitation>
). Near the town of 
<normalizedToken id="C8EA1EE0FE0AAC29C5D7176C40477AFA" originalValue="Contumazá">Contumaza</normalizedToken>
, it grows sympatrically with another shrubby 
<taxonomicName id="7E0507297F1A01339F44B806CEB9E806" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Cylindropuntia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Loasaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="48626D8190A345D136EC2C63AAC99213" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Nasa" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nasa macrothyrsa" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrothyrsa">
<emphasis id="7BC5FDD06519B3B43D9FB6E1AE698ED0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Nasa macrothyrsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Urb. &amp; Gilg) Weigend. These localities are surrounded by a mosaic of fields, fallows and small patches of seasonally dry montane forest according to the 
<bibRefCitation id="BF23A3EF83C5D360BD83E4B60F01B510" author="Ministerio del Ambiente del Peru" journalOrPublisher="Darwiniana" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" publicationUrl="https://geoservidor.minam.gob.pe/recursos/intercambio-de-datos/" refId="B16" refString="Ministerio del Ambiente del Peru, 2015. Mapa Nacional de Cobertura Vegetal. Ministerio del ambiente del Peru. https://geoservidor.minam.gob.pe/recursos/intercambio-de-datos/" title="Mapa Nacional de Cobertura Vegetal. Ministerio del ambiente del Peru." url="https://geoservidor.minam.gob.pe/recursos/intercambio-de-datos/" year="2015">
Ministerio del Ambiente del 
<normalizedToken id="EAFC74CB7D7B4D0906A4E56BF26E6603" originalValue="Perú">Peru</normalizedToken>
(2015
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="638F43F2A606D807A7B5A07F8630AF3E" author="Ministerio del Ambiente del Peru" journalOrPublisher="Darwiniana" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" publicationUrl="https://geoservidor.minam.gob.pe/recursos/intercambio-de-datos/" refId="B17" refString="Ministerio del Ambiente del Peru, 2018. Mapa Nacional de Ecosistemas. Ministerio del ambiente del Peru. https://geoservidor.minam.gob.pe/recursos/intercambio-de-datos/" title="Mapa Nacional de Ecosistemas. Ministerio del ambiente del Peru." url="https://geoservidor.minam.gob.pe/recursos/intercambio-de-datos/" year="2018">2018</bibRefCitation>
). These habitats often show signs of human alteration. 
<normalizedToken id="26A0F41C8C028A0BEB2648FA81DB52D1" originalValue="Rodríguez-">Rodriguez-</normalizedToken>
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B61098EB8A2DDE44DBC956D46241D" author="Rodriguez, EF" journalOrPublisher="Numero Especial" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" pagination="391 - 402" refId="B24" refString="Rodriguez, EF, Weigend, M, 2006. Loasaceae endemicas del Peru. Revista peruana de biologia. Numero Especial 13 (2): 391 - 402" title="Loasaceae endemicas del Peru. Revista peruana de biologia." volume="13" year="2006">
<normalizedToken id="FF71FFEACB4E185B725F8A79F811A487" originalValue="Rodríguez">Rodriguez</normalizedToken>
and Weigend (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
mention that this species is found in the Mesoandina Ecological Region. 
<taxonomicName id="421F1DE189080EC6481FF3B9E048B3B5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Xylopodia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xylopodia klaprothioides" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klaprothioides">
<emphasis id="0047ADB0E873DC2B3A09C169337B3F51" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Xylopodia klaprothioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is deciduous and the plants shed their leaves at the beginning of flowering in May/June.
</paragraph>
<caption id="22625A7D15859967C94AB022745EE843" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.194.77827.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/673021" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="059623EE843E14D230E90D1FD6ABBE26" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="2CD11B6652878DCC8F38F23886FDF7BD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Figure 4.</emphasis>
Habitats of 
<taxonomicName id="F1DE36F9032F746D0577A7841620C1F6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Xylopodia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xylopodia" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B2C760010FCF6390B9D0B4D1AE07663E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Xylopodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="AA367422D7489E744B4BAF204E81C7DF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">A</emphasis>
deciduous forest near Jujuy, Argentina, habitat of 
<taxonomicName id="C24FAFA81BB50DD4A57F0543D13DE0F9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="X." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="X. laurensis" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laurensis">
<emphasis id="9CD7BA14097F1BC119F2CDF964445C2B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. laurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F3A326C4AC634916EF4B947E4F4EBC46" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">B</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="9086C3B274EC21BEBCBC8CBABAB025CC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="X." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="X. laurensis" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laurensis">
<emphasis id="EC32B7B80AAB5033C3CB4AC215FD83A5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. laurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
habitat in a dry creek near Chuquisaca, Bolivia 
<emphasis id="37587BC4F35DE74CA03CDB3037994714" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">C</emphasis>
rocky slopes with xerophilous vegetation near the town of 
<normalizedToken id="D179222FE1F44FC6660A914B45EE03E4" originalValue="Contumazá">Contumaza</normalizedToken>
, Peru, habitat of narrowly endemic 
<taxonomicName id="CF4FBA4D48FA6C3584F976AFA9DACEA9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="X." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="X. klaprothioides" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klaprothioides">
<emphasis id="89FD02ADEE9EC89D919EDBE13DF58F45" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">X. klaprothioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="803AF62DAAEFA769B7673ACBA773CA5C" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="85F176B20E40425D73B2FD38316D7553" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BAD881F59F3A1C41F29B8F244363D743" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Flowering and fruiting of this species have been recorded at the very end of the rainy season and the start of the dry season in May and June; thus most plants are leafless during the peak of the flowering period.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
